Hi, who are you?

114
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Soot cup.

115
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Oh, how the same little creature.

116
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Is it about you? I don't trust him at all.

117
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
First time I've seen something like that.

118
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Is there anywhere to eat here? I'm very hungry.

119
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Oh, I'm sorry.

120
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:04,000
It must have been terrible to be confined in a cramped box.

121
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Little rascal. Moomin Mama gives you food.

122
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,000
I guess I came up with something.

123
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Oh, boys, he eats a lot.

124
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Good observation from a real big eater.

125
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Can I have more?

126
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Unfortunately, I don't have any more.

127
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Oh well, not then. Thanks for the deal.

128
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Come on, why were you sent here in the mail?

129
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,000
That was better than my mother.

130
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,000
What do you mean?

131
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Well, when mom complained that I'm going to make her another nervous wreck.

132
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,000
What could he mean?

133
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
I don't know. Not yet.

134
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,000
He couldn't take care of you.

135
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,000
You must have been so naughty that he thought of getting rid of you.

136
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,000
Well, why anyway?

137
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Selling was not a nice word.

138
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Well, I guess I'll live here with you from now on.

139
