154
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
If he stays, I'll go.

155
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,000
What the hell are we doing?

156
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:52,000
If he is too difficult a child for a mother, then what about us?

157
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,000
In fact, that's what I'm afraid of too.

158
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,000
Ha, I know an excellent breeder.

159
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,000
Well, I'm leaving now.

160
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,000
Don't get lost in the snow.

161
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,000
In.

162
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,000
Where are they taking me now?

163
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,000
Viljonkanluo.

164
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,000
She is a very nice and busy aunt and has three children of her own.

165
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,000
I'm used to being a punching bag.

166
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Anna, excuse me. Maybe I can pick you up after the snow has closed.

167
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Yeh, yeh. There's always an excuse.

168
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,000
